import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from scipy.stats import boxcox
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller
from statsmodels.tsa.seasonal import seasonal_decompose

In this assignment we perform decomposition of three time series datasets. We apply Box-Cox transformation, visualize original and transformed data, and decompose tha dataset into: trend, seasonal, and remainder components.

Helper Plots Functions

Formula for transformed: $\left\{\begin{matrix} Y(\lambda) = \frac{y_1^\lambda - 1 }{\lambda}, for \neq 0\\ Y(\lambda) = ln(y_i), for \lambda = 0\\ \end{matrix}\right.$

In[326]:
def transformed(df, column, list_xticks):
    y = df[column].dropna()
    y = pd.to_numeric(y, errors='coerce')

    # Added bias for negative numbers
    if (y <= 0).any():
        shift = abs(y.min()) + 1e-6
        y = y + shift
    y_box, lam = boxcox(y)

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 3))
    plt.plot(df.index[:len(y_box)], y_box,
             label=f'BoxCox ={lam:.2f}', color='green')
    plt.xticks(list_xticks, rotation=90)
    plt.legend()
    plt.title(f'Transformed {column} (BoxCox)')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
In[327]:
def origin_time_series(x, y, list_xticks):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 3))
    plt.plot(x, y, label='Original Time Series', color='yellow')
    plt.xticks(list_xticks, rotation=90)
    plt.legend()
In[328]:
def additive_trend(df, list_xticks, period=365):
    result_add = seasonal_decompose(df, period=period, model='additive')

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 3))
    plt.plot(result_add.trend.dropna(), label='Additive Trend', color='red')
    plt.xticks(list_xticks, rotation=90)
    plt.legend()
In[329]:
def additive_seasonal(df, list_xticks, period=365):
    result_add = seasonal_decompose(df, period=period, model='additive')

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 3))
    plt.plot(result_add.seasonal.dropna(), label='Additive Seasonal', color='purple')
    plt.xticks(list_xticks, rotation=90)
    plt.legend()
